Description:
This is a great ice-breaker if you have a long time to fill, especially with a larger group. The concept is similar to speed dating, but instead of meeting a bunch of people to try and date, players are meeting a bunch of other teens just to have fun playing games! Players will get the chance to quickly connect with as many others as you time for, possibly meeting everyone at your event. The game is a circle of games (board games, card games, &amp;amp; video games... best choices are common, simple games like Checkers, Jenga, Mariokart, scrabble, uno, etc.). Each game has multiple seats, with some seats on a numbered inside loop and some seats on a numbered outside loop. Have everyone take a seat at a game. Do a quick glance at the rules if needed, and then players face off and chat in the short time they have at their game. After a few minutes, a timer goes off and everyone must move one seat in the direction of their loop. Players meet new opponents on a new game (or possibly at a different position on the same game!), pick up where the last player left off, and continue on! Points are scored for completing a game or achieving something special like a Yahtzee or a double jump in checkers. Everyone keeps track of their own scores and creative prizes can be awarded at the end. Plan on 30-75 minutes depending on the size of your group.

This product comes with PDF instructions on how to set up the Speed Gaming, sample score cards and number cards, and some graphics for promo, as well as the original .ai Adobe Illustrator art files so you can modify the graphics as needed.

