When it comes to studying the character and attributes of God, no study has been more meaningful for my students than the Names of God. &nbsp;I have now taught through the Names of God series a couple times in my years of ministry, and it has always resulted in great conversation and solid theological learning.

Throughout the Old Testament, God receives multiple proper names. &nbsp;In almost every instance where God is given a name, the circumstances are miraculous and teach us something powerful about the character and provision of our God. &nbsp;Jehovah Jireh (The Lord Provides) was given when God provided a ram for Abraham's sacrifice instead of Isaac. &nbsp;Jehovah Rapha (The Lord Heals) was given when God healed the water at Marah so the Israelites could drink. &nbsp;These stories are just a taste of what the Names of God series will communicate to your students.

