Description:
This is a&nbsp;4-Week Series with sermon notes, social media graphics, and a leader training to prepare your ministry to talk about hard things. With all that students go through in life, they can face some really difficult situations. And too often, the church response is, 'hey, cheer up, Jesus loves you.' But what about the safety and permission to hurt? What about the God who comforts and is close to the brokenhearted? Here are four messages that look through the darker side of life, and where hope comes breaking through.

&lt;strong&gt;Light Breaking Through&lt;/strong&gt;: a 4 Week series called 'Light Breaking Through' all about finding hope in the darkest places in our lives.
&lt;ul&gt;
 	&lt;li&gt;Wk1: In the Shadow of Death (Depression: looking at Job 1-3 and Psalm 23)&lt;/li&gt;
 	&lt;li&gt;Wk2: Suicide is Not The Answer (Suicide: looking at 1 Kings 19)&lt;/li&gt;
 	&lt;li&gt;Wk3: Beyond Control (Circumstances beyond our control: looking at Job 1&amp;amp;2 again)&lt;/li&gt;
 	&lt;li&gt;Wk4: Death is Not the End (Death: looking at John 11)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Includes a training to prepare your leaders for what this series can (and most likely will) open up.&lt;/em&gt;

&lt;strong&gt;Leader training materials:&lt;/strong&gt; An in-depth training (should take about 2+ hours) for your leaders on the basics of Biblical Counseling, Mandatory Reporting, and Suicide Prevention.
&lt;ul&gt;
 	&lt;li&gt;4-page PDF with fill-ins for your leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
 	&lt;li&gt;4-page PDF with filled-in answers for you to lead it with.&lt;/li&gt;
 	&lt;li&gt;10-page notes to help you work through each point in the training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Series graphics:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
 	&lt;li&gt;1x 16:9 widescreen title slide (JPG)&lt;/li&gt;
 	&lt;li&gt;1x 16:9 widescreen notes slide (JPG)&nbsp;&lt;em&gt;You can add your notes on top of this, the series logo/graphic is in the bottom right.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 	&lt;li&gt;8x 1:1 square graphics to promote on social media like Instagram. Includes: A title slide, several of the key Bible verses from the messages, and a blank one to make your own. (JPG)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

